OL,3,GUK long range forecast
OL,4,
OL,5,COutlook for Tue 14 Jul to Thu 23 Jul
OL,6,FHigh pressure initially situated to
OL,7,Fthe north of the UK with low pressure
OL,8,Fover the Bay of Biscay starts the
OL,9,Fperiod with broadly settled weather
OL,10,Ffor much of the UK. There will,
OL,11,Fhowever, be a risk of thunderstorms
OL,12,Fspreading into the south of the UK
OL,13,Ffrom France at times. Through the
OL,14,Fweekend potentially turning more
OL,15,Funsettled with some rain or showers
OL,16,Fand thunderstorms at times as low
OL,17,Fpressure and a more northerly wind
OL,18,Faffect the UK at times. Temperatures
OL,19,Fwill be warm or very warm for most,
OL,20,Fperhaps hot at times in the southwest
OL,21,Finitially, likely easing to warm or
OL,22,Fnear average into the weekend, though
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,23,Ffurther hot spells possible between
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
OL,24,Fsystems.
